This tab goes over how to play the melodies and chords of 'I Promise' making use of different strumming and fretting hand techniques such as the drone note technique and the thumb over the neck chord forming technique. Keep an eye out for the lyrical cues for each section of the song which help make this tab easier to follow along with. If you need further instruction on how to follow this tab, visit this YouTube link for a tutorial with in depth descriptions and exercises to build up to the techniques used in this song: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zs_IoicplhY.

This video guitar lesson for I Promise by Radiohead simplifies the movements within the melodies and slowly eases into playing the song accurately in real time with the interesting guitar techniques used in the song. The techniques this lesson focuses on include the drone note technique used to create the nice deep melodic sound of the verse and the thumb over the neck chord forming technique which allows you to have a moving melody along with your chords in the chorus section. The pacing of the lesson is designed to be accessible towards beginners but the description under the YouTube video includes time stamps for those that would like to look ahead to a certain section of the lesson or a specific part of the song.

version_description: A simple no frills tab and it sounds good on the ukulele. In 6/8 time signature so a waltz (123, 123, 123) strum pattern works well: D UDUD UDUD UDUD UDU. CAPO on the 2nd Fret to play along with the original album recording. The intro is a standard G shape fingering starting at the fifth fret and moving down 1 fret at a time until you reach the G chord. The G string always remains open. For the bridge, the chord defined as "A7" at the end of the bridge and chorus 1 is actually G chord but with the C string finger moved down one fret to give a C# root note (producing a dissonant non-defined chord) but an A7 is almost as good.
